The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Lal in hospital   with dengue
                                                                                                                       7                                      Lal in hospital   with dengue
            A STAFF REPORTER                            
	Calcutta: Former India opener Arun Lal is in the intensive care unit of a hospital in Colombo with dengue.         
	He has been running a temperature for the sixth day, on Tuesday. But in a text message to The Telegraph, Lal hoped that the worst was over, and he would soon be fine.         
	Lal is there on a television commentary assignment. He played 16 Tests for India and scored 729 runs at an average of 26.03. He also played 13 one-day Internationals.                                                                                                                     
